@Strudel Dad 

I used to work in a warehouse just off the southernmost runway of Hartsville-Jackson in Atlanta. We ended up with a coping method that was never discussed, but always observed: once the noise of an approaching jet was approaching the point where we would have had to shout to be heard, we stopped speaking on that word and just looked at each other until it subsided, then picked up the sentence right where we'd left off.

For unknown-to-us reasons, about half of those jets using that runway were sky-blue windowless KLM cargo 747s, and some of them came in very low. If we were standing outside we could see the pilots' faces.

